==================================================================================================================================================

 - FEATURES AND IMPORTANT INFORMATION - !

==================================================================================================================================================

..................................................................................................................................................

 - In Konsole there's a list of quick commands provided in [ - Commands - ]
 
 - The command [ optional ] installs optional packages for Algiz, this is useful if you have a laptop.
 
 - Enter the command [ nmtui ] to connect to the internet.

 - To update all of your system's packages at once run the command [ update ]

 - If you want to update Algiz to the newest version, run the command [ update-algiz ]

 - Algiz uses an automatic MAC address changer upon login.

 - All DNS traffic is encrypted through [ dnscrypt-proxy ] via Mullvad which prevents DNS leaks.

 - The [ steal ] command installs packages from the default repo, AUR and Flatpak. It also can download videos.
 
 - On laptops the maximum charge is 79% to preserve the battery.
 
 - Expect slower application launches on laptop until preloader caches frequently used applications.
 
 - Adjust your screen brightness to 60% to conserve battery life.
 
 - When connecting a charger to a laptop, system performance will increase when the battery is at 79%.

 - Change shaders to Vulkan in Steam settings and enable Steam Play for Linux compatibility.

 - Use [ GloriousEggroll ] which is provided with Algiz as your proton prefix for Steam.

 - To get more FPS for games copy & paste [ gamemoderun %command% ] in launch options which is found through properties in Steam.

..................................................................................................................................................

==================================================================================================================================================






==================================================================================================================================================

 - COMMANDS AND WHAT THEY MEAN - !

==================================================================================================================================================

..................................................................................................................................................

 / SUPER USER /

 . su

..................................................................................................................................................

 / PACKAGE DICTIONARY /
 
 . pd

 - This command searches Pacman, AUR and Flatpak for specific packages based off keywords.
 
 - Press Q to leave the enviroment.

..................................................................................................................................................

 / INSTALL PACKAGES AND DOWNLOAD VIDEOS /

 . steal [ PACKAGE ]
 
 OR
 
 . steal [URL1] [URL2]

 - This command will download system packages, music, videos and livestreams. 
 
 - You can download multiple URLs if they're separated by spaces.
 
 . latest [ PACKAGE ]
 
 - This command doesn't cycle, used for rare package version conflicts.
 
..................................................................................................................................................

 / UNINSTALL PACKAGES /

 . remove [ PACKAGE ]

..................................................................................................................................................

 / FORCE PACKAGE INSTALL /

 . force [ PACKAGE ]
 
 - This should only be used in rare circumstances.

..................................................................................................................................................

 / ROLLBACK PACKAGE /

 . rollback [ PACKAGE ]

..................................................................................................................................................

 / UPDATE SYSTEM /

 . update

 - This command updates the system's packages.
 
..................................................................................................................................................

 / UPDATE ALGIZ /

 . update-algiz
 
 - This command updates Algiz to it's newest configuration.

..................................................................................................................................................

 / KEYWORD SEARCH /

 . ks
 
 - This command finds keywords in a directory quickly.

..................................................................................................................................................

 / CHECK VERSION /

 . version [ PACKAGE ]
 
 - This command is used to check the version of a package.

..................................................................................................................................................

 / CLEAN UNUSED & OLD PACKAGES /

 . clean

..................................................................................................................................................

 / CHANGE DIRECTORY /

 . cd [ /EXAMPLE/EXAMPLE ]
 
 - If the directory has a space [ /EXAMPLE/EXAMPLE FOLDER ] use
 
 . cd [ '/EXAMPLE/EXAMPLE FOLDER' ]

..................................................................................................................................................

 / LOAD PYTHON SCRIPT /
 
 . p [ DIRECTORY TO .py FILE ]
 
 - Example: p /home/1.py

..................................................................................................................................................

 / DEFINE COMMAND /

 . man [ COMMAND ]

..................................................................................................................................................

 / ACCESS ADMIN FILE MANAGER /

 . su -c'thunar'

..................................................................................................................................................

 / LIST ATTACHED DRIVES /

 . lsblk

..................................................................................................................................................

 / FIND UUID /
 
 . doas lsblk -f

..................................................................................................................................................

 / VIEW COMPUTER SPECS /

 . neofetch

..................................................................................................................................................

 / LIST MAC ADDRESSES AND NETWORK DEVICES /

 . ip link show

..................................................................................................................................................

 / AUDIT SECURITY OF SYSTEM /

 . doas lynis audit system

..................................................................................................................................................

 / ADD S6 SERVICES /

 . s6-service add default [ SERVICE ]

 . s6-db-reload

..................................................................................................................................................

 / LIST INSTALLED PACKAGES /

 . doas pacman -Qe

..................................................................................................................................................

 / RELOAD S6 /

 . s6-db-reload
 
..................................................................................................................................................

 / ANTIVIRUS /
 
 . antivirus
 
 - This command uses ClamAV to scan your whole system and automatically removes suspected malware.

..................................................................................................................................................

 / ARCHIVIST TOOLS COMMANDS /
 
 > https://github.com/Michael-Sebero/Archivist-Tools

..................................................................................................................................................

 / DOCUMENT TOOLS COMMANDS /
 
 > https://github.com/Michael-Sebero/Document-Tools
 
..................................................................................................................................................

 / MEDIA TOOLS COMMANDS /
 
 > https://github.com/Michael-Sebero/Media-Tools
 
..................................................................................................................................................

 / GAME FOCUS /
 
 . game-focus

 - The command [ game-focus ] kills your desktop environment and launches Steam in big picture mode.
  
..................................................................................................................................................

 / TIMED SHUTOFF /
 
 . timed-shutoff
 
 - This command shuts off your PC in a specified amount of time.

..................................................................................................................................................

 / REFRESH KEYRING /

 . refresh-keyring
 
 - This command refreshes your pacman keyring.

..................................................................................................................................................

 / WINEDIR /
 
 . winedir

 - This command converts a Linux directory into to a Wine directory.
 
 - Example: home/frank/folder > z:\home\frank\folder\
 
..................................................................................................................................................

 / DISABLE IPV6 /
 
 . disable-ipv6
 
 . disable-ipv6-perm

..................................................................................................................................................

 / ALARM /
 
 . alarm
 
..................................................................................................................................................

 / REPAIR SYSTEM /
 
 . repair-system
 
 - This command is a troubleshooting tool for Algiz.
 
..................................................................................................................................................

 / PLAN S /
 
 . plan-s
 
 - This command deletes all of your system files and makes them mostly unrecoverable.
 
..................................................................................................................................................

 / FORMAT TO XFS /
 
 . format-to-xfs
 
 - After formatting adjust the permissions of the newly formatted drive to sudo chmod 777 [ /dev/formatteddrive ]

..................................................................................................................................................

 / FORMAT TO ZFS /
 
 . format-to-zfs
 
 - After formatting adjust the permissions of the newly formatted drive to sudo chmod 777 [ /dev/formatteddrive ]
 
..................................................................................................................................................

 / FIX CLOCK /
 
 . fix-clock
 
 - This command fixes issues with your system's clock.
 
..................................................................................................................................................

  / AUDIO FREQUENCY TOOLS /

  . audio-frequency-tools
  
  - This command lets you generate, detect audio frequencies and much more.
  
..................................................................................................................................................

 / FIX CORRUPT /
 
 . fix-corrupt

 - This command fixes corrupt packages in the system.

..................................................................................................................................................

 / REINSTALL-ALL /
 
 . reinstall-all

 - This command reinstalls all packages in the system.

..................................................................................................................................................

 / FIND FAST MIRRORLISTS /
 
 . fastlist
 
 - This command disables slow pacman mirrorlists and enables fast ones according to your location.
 
.................................................................................................................................................. 

 / DATA RECOVERY TOOLS /
 
 . data-recovery-tools
 
 - This command attempts to recover data from damaged devices and corrupted files.

..................................................................................................................................................

 / META /
 
 . meta
 
 - This script takes a media file path (from an argument or user input) and outputs detailed metadata about the file using ffprobe.
 
..................................................................................................................................................

 / FORCE UPDATE /
 
 . force-update
 
 - This command forces a system update without dependency checks.
 
..................................................................................................................................................

